# Render Preview PR Attestation Gate

For pull requests targeting `main` where Render previews are used:

- PR title must include `[render preview]`.
- A committed `.ci/render-live-attestation.json` must exist and validate.
- The attestation must be fresh, tied to the PR head SHA, and report all live checks passed.

## Enforcement expectations

- Treat `Render Preview Attestation Gate` GitHub Actions failures as blocking.
- Do not report a PR as merge-ready until preview deploy status is healthy/live and attestation validation passes.
- If validation fails, refresh live checks against the current preview environment, regenerate/update `.ci/render-live-attestation.json`, and re-run verification.
- When discovering preview URLs, commit SHAs on preview services, or deploy status, use **Render MCP** (see **render-deploy-monitor-and-debug**): e.g. **`list_services`** with **`includePreviews`: true**, then **`list_deploys`** / **`get_deploy`** for the matching `… PR #<n>` services—prefer **`project-0-vecinita-render`** when enabled, else **`plugin-render-render`** after auth/workspace selection.
